description:
The invincible Pluto sets out to kill the seven strongest robots in the world and become king of the robots. Its the duty of Astro Boy, Japans resident boy robot, to stop Pluto from wreaking havoc and killing more robots. In Phoenix: Karma, the crippled bandit Gao meets a mysterious old man who tells him he will die in three yearsby a nose disease of all things! And Dororo opens up with a story of a power-starved man who sacrifices his son for infinite power. Also included is the story of Black Jack, the most infamously expensive and morally ambiguous doctor around.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Greatest Robot On Earth Chapter One
  • Phoenix: Karma Chapter One
  • Dororo: The Incepition
  • Black Jack: Is There A Doctor?
name: Vol. 1

description:
Tezuka introduces his new story Buddha, where the Brahmin live lavishly and comfortably on the top of the social hierarchy, at the expense of its plebeians. When slave boy Chapra seeks out the beggar Tatta to recover his masters stolen goods, they form an uneasy comradeship. In this rigid class-dictated society, is survival a matter of playing by the rules or rebelling against authority? Also included are the continuations of Astro Boy and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Greatest Robot On Earth Chapter Two
  • Buddha: Part One - Brahmin
  • Black Jack: U-18 Knew
name: Vol. 2

description:
This issue introduces the new series Dororo! Hyakkimaru is an empty man, in quite a literal sense. He has no eyes, no ears, and instead of arms he has two swords attached to his shoulders. On a whim, he saves a young thief named Dororo from a group of ruffians. However, instead of receiving undying gratitude from the young boy, he gets a declaration threatening his sword! Also included are the continuations of Astro Boy and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Greatest Robot On Earth Chapter Three
  • Dororo: Hyakkimaru
  • Black Jack: Teratoid Cystoma
name: Vol. 3

description:
As Pluto nears the completion of his goal, urgency may force Astro Boy to into a dangerous decision. The narrative of good and evil becomes increasingly more ambiguous and less of a given. In Phoenix: Karma, a man finds his humanity in the face of his crimes while bitterness fosters inside another when his head is given a deadline. The magazine wraps up with the young Black Jacks love story!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Greatest Robot On Earth Chapter Four
  • Phoenix: Karma Chapter Two
  • Black Jack: Confluence
name: Vol. 4

description:
In the newly featured Adolf, a Japanese news reporter comes to Berlin in the midst of the 1936 Olympics, Germanys rise to power, Hitlers reign, and the mysterious death of his brother. As he delves deeper into uncovering the truth, he finds himself descending into a web a politics, conspiracy and intolerance. Also included in this volume is Hyakkimarus past in Dororo, an unsatisfied patient in Black Jack, and a showdown between the newly enhanced Astro Boy and Pluto in Astro Boy.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Greatest Robot On Earth Chapter Five
  • Adolf: A Tale of the Twentieth Century Chapter One
  • Dororo: The Monk
  • Black Jack: The First Storm of Spring
name: Vol. 5

description:
What defines evil? What defines strong? Osamu Tezuka continues to challenge the archetypes of the black villain and the white hero in his classic, Astro Boy. In Buddha, Naradatta finally finds the Tatta of the prophecies, who is nothing like he expected. Also included are Dororo, where the two friends casually pass towns and encounter a suspicious noblewoman who is respected by all, and Black Jack, which features the meeting between Pinoko and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Greatest Robot On Earth Chapter Six
  • Buddha: Part One - Tatta the Urchin
  • Dororo: Kanekozo
  • Black Jack: Teratoid Cystoma
name: Vol. 6

description:
In Adolf, Toge comes closer than ever to the details of his brothers death. However, the more questions he solves, the more questions he has to answer. Tezukas take on political conspiracy in Nazi Germany questions whether deception and sincerity are mutually exclusive. Also included are Astro Boy and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Greatest Robot On Earth Chapter Seven
  • Adolf: A Tale of the Twentieth Century Chapter Two
  • Black Jack: Star, Magnitude Six
name: Vol. 7

description:
Astro Boy goes to Mount Aso to fight the conclusive battle with Pluto and retrieve Dr. Ochanomizu. But suddenly a new foe appears, claiming hes the strongest robot on earth! Will this turn of events play out better for Astro Boy, or simply make things more complicated? Also included are the stories Adolf, where a friendship transcends the most brutal form of racism, Phoenix: Karma, which reveals the unsavory truth of religion, and Black Jack, where motivation comes from a bit a nostalgia.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Greatest Robot On Earth Chapter Eight
  • Adolf: A Tale of the Twentieth Century Chapter Three
  • Phoenix: Karma Chapter Three
  • Black Jack: The Legs of An Ant
name: Vol. 8

description:
Stay tuned for the finale of the Pluto arc! Pluto and Astro Boy finally have their showdown. However, Astro Boy would rather work out their differences and talk, but Pluto has an unwavering determination to complete his goal. Will the two ever be able to reconcile their differences for once and for all or will their relationship end in a decisive battle? Also included are Buddha, Dororo, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Greatest Robot On Earth Chapter Nine
  • Buddha Part One: General Budai
  • Dororo: Bandai
  • Black Jack: Sometimes Like Pearls
name: Vol. 9

description:
Its Machine Day in Astro Boy! All the robots get to rest on this prominent holiday and take time to kick back and relax. However, not all humans are happy about giving the machines some time off. The mysterious Dr. Foola offers to show those robots their place for a hefty sum of 1 billion yen, but how will he manage it? The opponents of Machine Day might get more than their moneys worth! Also included are Buddha, Phoenix: Karma, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Mad Machine
  • Buddha: Part One The Announcement
  • Phoenix: Karma Chapter Four
  • Black Jack: Black Queen
name: Vol. 10

description:
After saving the general's life, Buddha's Chapra becomes his adopted son and trains with the royal guard in the hopes of someday succeeding his adopted father's revered position. But what happens when the general finds out he is really a slave, the lowest social caste not even worthy of being looked at by a common man? Meanwhile, Chapra's real mother travels the desert in search of her son, but she and her friends are quickly running out of supplies. In order to get some food, one of them will have to be sacrificed to a giant snake if any of them are to see their destination! Also included are Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps, a tale of cyborgs, dogs, and cyborg dogs and the continuations of Dororo and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps Chapter One
  • Buddha: Part One - Chapra
  • Dororo: The Face Tumor
  • Black Jack: Two Loves
name: Vol. 11

description:
In the second installment of Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps, Astro Boy manages to put a tracking device on the person who may have stolen Pero, his teacher's faithful dog. Let's hope they can get to Pero in time! In Buddha, the Kosala Kingdom is holding a contest to decide the strongest warrior in the land, and Prince Chapra will be fighting to prove himself against many other men. There are claims he is the best archer in the world, but can he hold his own against all the other warriors? Also included are the continuations of Phoenix: Karma and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps Chapter Two
  • Buddha: Part One - The King's Cup
  • Phoenix: Karma Chapter Five
  • Black Jack: The Painting Is Dead!
name: Vol. 12

description:
In Buddha, Queen Maya prepares to give birth while miraculous omens occur one by one in the kingdom of Shakya. In the blistering heat of April, the banks of the river do not dry, and fish, birds, and beasts alike gather to see the queen off on her journey. King Suddhodana predicts that his wife will give birth to an extraordinary child with a destiny greater than kingshipbut will tragedy mar this joyous occasion? Also included are the continuations of Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps, Adolf, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps Three
  • Buddha: Part One - The Birth
  • Adolf: A Tale of the Twentieth Century Chapter Four
  • Black Jack: Needle
name: Vol. 13

description:
Japan's Yashima Space Rocket explodes en route to the moon, and it looks like a force from Earth is responsible! Astro Boy follows the culprit's trail to the Bering Strait, where our hero's reconnaissance uncovers a shocking plot. Meanwhile, in Dororo: The Misery Chronicles, Dororo recounts his past struggles to Hyakkimaru. Demons and ghosts mock Dororo's tale of woe, but the young bandit isn't so easily fazed! Also included are the continuation of Buddha and another tale of the unorthodox doctor, Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps Four
  • Buddha Part One: The Contest
  • Dororo: The Misery Chronicles
  • Black Jack: Granny
name: Vol. 14

description:
Complications arise in Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps as the faithful dog Pero, now transformed into a humanoid robot, tries to go back to his master, who doesn't recognize him. Later in the volume, Black Jack tells the tragic story of Black Jack's old friend, a killer whale named Triton, who used to frequent the bay where the doctor lived. Also included are the continuations of Buddha and Phoenix: Karma.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps Five
  • Buddha Part One: All For A Cure
  • Phoenix: Karma Chapter Six
  • Black Jack: The Ballad of the Killer Whale
name: Vol. 15

description:
This issue's installment of Astro Boy The Hot Dog Corps reveals the true nature of the cyborg known as #44 and his struggle to come to terms with what he learns. Later, Buddha opens with the birth of Prince Siddharta, whom the wisest man in the land prophesies is destined for greatness! Meanwhile, Naradatta is punished harshly for his cruel treatment of animals, even if it was to save Chapra's life. Also included are Adolf and the continuation of Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps Six
  • Buddha Part One: The Prophecy
  • Adolf: A Tale of the Twentieth Century Chapter Five
  • Black Jack: To Each His Own
name: Vol. 16

description:
In part 7 of Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps, Astro Boy finds both peril and an unexpected ally in his fight against the evil Dr. Junkovitch. Then in Black Jack, our mysterious doctor has a reputation as the greediest surgeon around, charging clients millions of yen for his miracle-working services -- but has the he finally met a man whose avarice outstrips his own? Also included are the continuing adventures of Chapra in Buddha and Hyakkimaru in Dororo.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps Seven
  • Buddha Part One: The Judgment
  • Dororo: The Possessed Sword
  • Black Jack: Emergency Shelter
name: Vol. 17

description:
In Phoenix: Karma, Akanemaru and Gao's paths converge once more as the two men, both renowned artists, battle for the right to sculpt gargoyles for the temple's roof. In a heated contest that pits the genius against genius, Akanemaru struggles to reawaken his dormant muse while Gao receives a sobering vision and a message of hope from the Phoenix; in the end, who will win the ultimate honor? Also included are Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps, Buddha, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps Eight
  • Buddha Part One: The Wall of Death
  • Phoenix: Karma Chapter Seven
  • Black Jack: Dirtjacked
name: Vol. 18

description:
In Buddha, young prince Siddhartha questions his world's caste system and values as he grows. He's a frail, sickly boy, but he is kind-- and that doesn't seem to agree with a lot of his elders. How is he supposed to become a king who can uphold these laws he hates? How can he be a warrior when he can't stand even to hunt small animals? Unhappy and alone in his views, Siddhartha begins to question his destiny. Also included are Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps, Black Jack, and Adolf.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps Nine
  • Buddha Part Two: The Prince
  • Adolf: A Tale of the Twentieth Century Chapter Six
  • Black Jack: Where Art Thou, Friend?
name: Vol. 19

description:
In Black Jack, the president of Cainan suffers an attempt on his life and is seriously injured. With a bullet lodged in their leader's brain, Cainan's government officials call the only doctor skilled enough to have a shot at removing it, Dr. Black Jack himself. But can the mysterious doctor really perform such a complicated operation successfully? With the assassins targeting him as well, his chances don't look good! Also included in this issue are Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps, Buddha, and the first installment of Dororo: Banmon.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Hot Dog Corps Ten
  • Buddha Part Two: The Garden of Meditation
  • Dororo: Banmon Chapter One
  • Black Jack: Kidnapping
name: Vol. 20

description:
This issue of Astro Boy features one of Tezuka's personal favorite short works, Plant People. A strange boy from an alien planet appears before Astro Boy with a warning-- Earth will be attacked by aliens! Will the alert be enough for Astro Boy to help save the day as the alien spaceships start stealing Earth's water supply? Also included are Buddha, Phoenix: Karma, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Plant People
  • Buddha Part Two: The Rapids
  • Phoenix: Karma Chapter Eight
  • Black Jack: Assembly Line Care
name: Vol. 21

description:
When an unexpected friend saves Black Jack from being wrongly accused of murder, the doctor promises to repay the kindness in any way he can. But when his friend needs him most, Black Jack finds himself halfway across the country! Will he make it in time to save the life of the man who saved his? Also included in this issue are Astro Boy: White Planet, Adolf, and Buddha.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: White Planet
  • Buddha Part Two: Yashodara
  • Adolf: An Exile In Japan Chapter One
  • Black Jack: Helping Each Other
name: Vol. 22

description:
This issue opens with the first chapter of Astro Boy: His Highness Deadcross, featuring the story of Gravia, a country run by the first robot president. Unfortunately, not everyone is pleased with the election of a robot, and Gravia needs Astro's help! Will he be able to save the president from being attacked and destroyed? And who is this Deadcross, anyway? Also included are Buddha, Dororo, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: His Highness Deadcross Chapter One
  • Buddha Part Two: Migaila Chapter One
  • Dororo: Banmon Chapter Two
  • Black Jack: Stradivarius
name: Vol. 23

description:
In Astro Boy: His Highness Deadcross, Deadcross has kidnapped Astro's teacher! And Astro Boy has no idea what tortures his poor teacher is suffering, not even realizing Mustachio had followed him to Gravia! Will Astro Boy be able to help both the president of Gravia and his hapless teacher in time? Also included are Buddha, Black Jack, and the first chapter of Phoenix: Dawn.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: His Highness Deadcross Chapter Two
  • Buddha Part Two: Migaila Chapter Two
  • Phoenix: Dawn Chapter One
  • Black Jack: Pinoko's Challenge
name: Vol. 24

description:
In Astro Boy: His Highness Deadcross, the Deadcross society trying to get rid of the robot president Rag attacks during Rag's big speech! Thousands of people are watching, Rag is in danger, and Mustachio is still being held hostage... Astro Boy might be able to hold his own against the attacking robots, but what will he do when Rag suddenly gets kidnapped too?! Also included are Black Jack, Buddha, and Adolf.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: His Highness Deadcross Chapter Three
  • Buddha Part Two: The Four Encounters Chapter One
  • Adolf: An Exile In Japan Chapter Two
  • Black Jack: Hospital Jack
name: Vol. 25
